---
import SidebarLayout from '../../../layouts/SidebarLayout.astro';
import "../../../styles/global.css";
---

<SidebarLayout app="javascript">
  <h1 class="text-xl sm:text-3xl font-bold mb-5 text-custom-accent text-center">
    JavaScript Tutorials
  </h1>

  <section class="mb-5 space-y-6 text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed text-custom-secondary">
    <p>
      <strong class="text-custom-primary">JavaScript</strong> is the programming language of the web. It enables interactive web pages and is an essential part of web development alongside HTML and CSS.
    </p>

    <p>
      Originally created to make web pages alive, JavaScript has evolved into a versatile language used for front-end development, back-end development, mobile apps, and even desktop applications.
    </p>

    <p>
      In this tutorial series, you'll learn:
    </p>

    <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 pl-4">
      <li>JavaScript syntax and fundamentals</li>
      <li>DOM manipulation and event handling</li>
      <li>Modern ES6+ features</li>
      <li>Asynchronous programming</li>
      <li>Object-oriented programming in JavaScript</li>
      <li>Working with APIs and JSON</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="bg-custom-secondary border border-custom rounded-2xl p-4 sm:p-6 mt-6">
      <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold text-custom-accent mb-3">Why Learn JavaScript?</h2>
      <p>
        JavaScript is the most popular programming language in the world. It runs in every web browser and has a massive ecosystem of libraries and frameworks. Learning JavaScript opens doors to full-stack development.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-3">
        With Node.js, JavaScript can be used for server-side development, making it possible to build complete web applications using a single programming language.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</SidebarLayout>